## Setup Requirements

**Dependencies:** Ruby >= 3.2.0, Bundler, Git CLI, dev-handbook submodule

**Setup:** `cd dev-tools && bundle install`

## Gem Executables

### `search` – Fast unified search for files and content
<details><summary>Details</summary>

```bash
search [PATTERN] [OPTIONS]
```

**Key flags:** `--files` (file search), `--preset NAME` (use preset), `--fzf` (interactive)

**Example:**
```bash
search "TODO" --preset todo  # Find all TODO comments
```
</details>

### `agent-lint` – Lint agent definition files
<details><summary>Details</summary>

**Key flags:** `--fix` (auto-fix), `--strict` (strict mode)  
**Example:** `agent-lint agents/*.ag.md --fix`
</details>

### `capture-it` – Capture project ideas and notes
<details><summary>Details</summary>

**Key flags:** `--type TYPE` (note type), `--priority LEVEL` (priority)  
**Example:** `capture-it "Feature idea" --type idea`
</details>

### `code-lint` – Lint code files with autofix
<details><summary>Details</summary>

**Key flags:** `--fix` (auto-fix), `--type LANG` (language)  
**Example:** `code-lint lib/**/*.rb --fix`
</details>

### `code-review` – Preset-based code review
<details><summary>Details</summary>

**Key flags:** `--preset NAME` (preset), `--model NAME` (model)  
**Example:** `code-review --preset pr --model google:gemini-2.0-flash-exp`
</details>

### `code-review-synthesize` – Review synthesis tool
<details><summary>Details</summary>

**Key flags:** `--format TYPE` (format), `--include-recommendations` (recommendations)  
**Example:** `code-review-synthesize --format report --include-recommendations`
</details>

### `context` – Load project context presets
<details><summary>Details</summary>

**Key flags:** `--preset NAME` (context preset), `--list` (list presets)  
**Example:** `context --preset dev-tools`
</details>

### `coverage-analyze` – Code coverage analysis
<details><summary>Details</summary>

**Key flags:** `--format TYPE` (report format), `--threshold NUM` (threshold)  
**Example:** `coverage-analyze --format html --threshold 90`
</details>

### `create-path` – Create files/directories with templates
<details><summary>Details</summary>

**Key flags:** `--force` (overwrite), `--template PATH` (template)  
**Example:** `create-path file README.md --content "# My Project"`
</details>

### `git-add` – Enhanced git add
<details><summary>Details</summary>
**Key flags:** `--patch` (interactive), `--all` (add all)  
**Example:** `git-add --patch`
</details>

### `git-checkout` – Enhanced git checkout
<details><summary>Details</summary>
**Key flags:** `--create` (create branch), `--force` (force)  
**Example:** `git-checkout feature-branch --create`
</details>

### `git-commit` – Enhanced git commit
<details><summary>Details</summary>
**Key flags:** `--intention TEXT` (intention), `--no-edit` (skip editor)  
**Example:** `git-commit --intention "fix typo" --no-edit`
</details>

### `git-fetch` – Enhanced git fetch
<details><summary>Details</summary>
**Key flags:** `--all` (all remotes), `--prune` (cleanup)  
**Example:** `git-fetch --all --prune`
</details>

### `git-log` – Enhanced git log
<details><summary>Details</summary>
**Key flags:** `--oneline` (compact), `--graph` (show graph)  
**Example:** `git-log --oneline --graph`
</details>

### `git-mv` – Enhanced git move
<details><summary>Details</summary>
**Key flags:** `--force` (force), `--dry-run` (preview)  
**Example:** `git-mv old-file.rb new-file.rb`
</details>

### `git-pull` – Enhanced git pull
<details><summary>Details</summary>
**Key flags:** `--rebase` (rebase), `--ff-only` (fast-forward)  
**Example:** `git-pull --rebase`
</details>

### `git-push` – Enhanced git push
<details><summary>Details</summary>
**Key flags:** `--force` (force), `--set-upstream` (set tracking)  
**Example:** `git-push --set-upstream origin feature-branch`
</details>

### `git-restore` – Enhanced git restore
<details><summary>Details</summary>
**Key flags:** `--staged` (from index), `--worktree` (working tree)  
**Example:** `git-restore --staged file.rb`
</details>

### `git-rm` – Enhanced git remove
<details><summary>Details</summary>
**Key flags:** `--cached` (index only), `--force` (force)  
**Example:** `git-rm --cached unwanted-file.log`
</details>

### `git-status` – Enhanced git status
<details><summary>Details</summary>
**Key flags:** `--verbose` (detailed), `--short` (compact)  
**Example:** `git-status --verbose`
</details>

### `git-switch` – Enhanced git switch
<details><summary>Details</summary>
**Key flags:** `--create` (create), `--force-create` (force create)  
**Example:** `git-switch main`
</details>

### `git-tag` – Enhanced git tag
<details><summary>Details</summary>
**Key flags:** `--annotate` (annotated), `--delete` (delete)  
**Example:** `git-tag v1.2.3 --annotate`
</details>

### `handbook` – Development handbook access
<details><summary>Details</summary>
**Key flags:** `sync-templates` (sync), `claude` (integration)  
**Example:** `handbook sync-templates`
</details>

### `llm-query` – Unified LLM query interface
<details><summary>Details</summary>
**Key flags:** `--model NAME` (model), `--output FILE` (save output)  
**Example:** `llm-query google:gemini-2.5-flash "What is Ruby?"`
</details>

### `mcp-proxy` – MCP server proxy
<details><summary>Details</summary>
**Key flags:** `--port NUM` (port), `--config FILE` (config)  
**Example:** `mcp-proxy --port 3000 --config mcp.yml`
</details>

### `nav-ls` – Enhanced directory listing
<details><summary>Details</summary>
**Key flags:** `--long` (detailed), `--all` (show hidden)  
**Example:** `nav-ls --long --all docs/`
</details>

### `nav-path` – Intelligent path navigation
<details><summary>Details</summary>
**Key flags:** `task` (resolve task ID), `file` (find file)  
**Example:** `nav-path file blueprint`
</details>

### `nav-tree` – Enhanced project tree
<details><summary>Details</summary>
**Key flags:** `--context TYPE` (context), `--depth NUM` (depth)  
**Example:** `nav-tree --context dev --depth 3`
</details>

### `reflection-synthesize` – Reflection report generator
<details><summary>Details</summary>
**Key flags:** `--session ID` (session), `--focus AREAS` (focus areas)  
**Example:** `reflection-synthesize --session current --focus architecture`
</details>

### `release-manager` – Release management tool
<details><summary>Details</summary>
**Key flags:** `current` (show current), `report` (generate report)  
**Example:** `release-manager current`
</details>

### `task-manager` – Project task management
<details><summary>Details</summary>
**Key flags:** `--filter EXPR` (filter), `--limit NUM` (max results)  
**Example:** `task-manager next --filter priority:high --limit 3`
</details>

## Tool Categories

### By Function
* **Code Review**: `code-review`, `code-review-synthesize`
* **Code Quality**: `agent-lint`, `code-lint`, `coverage-analyze`
* **Git Operations**: `git-add`, `git-commit`, `git-fetch`, `git-log`, `git-pull`, `git-push`, `git-status`, `git-tag`
* **LLM Integration**: `llm-query`, `mcp-proxy`
* **Navigation**: `nav-ls`, `nav-path`, `nav-tree`
* **Project Management**: `release-manager`, `task-manager`, `capture-it`
* **Development Tools**: `context`, `create-path`, `handbook`

### By Persona
* **AI Agent**: `llm-query`, `nav-path`, `release-manager`, `task-manager`
* **Human Developer**: `code-review`, `handbook`, `code-lint`, `coverage-analyze`
* **Git Power-User**: `git-add`, `git-commit`, `git-status`, `git-tag`
* **Release Manager**: `release-manager`, `task-manager`

## Common Workflows

### AI Agent Workflow
```bash
task-manager next
nav-path task 42
nav-path file blueprint
llm-query google "How to implement feature X?"
```

### Human Developer Workflow
```bash
handbook sync-templates
code-review --preset pr
task-manager recent
reflection-synthesize --session current
```

### Git Power-User Workflow
```bash
git-status --verbose
git-commit --intention "update features"
git-push
```

## Notes

* All tools available directly by name via fish integration
* Use `tool-name --help` for detailed usage information
* Git wrappers provide enhanced functionality over standard git commands

*For the most up-to-date information, run individual tools with `--help` flag.*
